Action]]\n|Tom Struthers\n|{{Won}}\n|}\n\n==Graphic novels==\n* A grapc  titled ''Ek Tha Tiger: Mahasagar Ki Suraksha'' (English: ''Ek Tha Tiger: Saving The High Seas'') was published in 2012 by [[Yomics]]. Post release, the comic failed to generate a positive word-of-mouth. Joginder Tuteja of [[Bollywood Hungama]] commended the comics' design but said that the main story failed to meet his expectations of a deeper plot, exciting narrative and a tighter script.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/3809 |title=Comic book Review: Ek Tha Tiger \u2013 Dhoom Redux 893 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |date=10 August 2012 |accessdate=15 August 2012}}</ref>\n* Another graphic novel named ''Ek Tha Tiger: Caught In The Web'' has been published in 2012 by Yomics, which also features some ''[[Hum Tum]]'' characters.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://yomics.in/Comics/9/Ek-Tha-Tiger-New |title=Archived copy |access-date=21 September 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112212115/http://yomics.in/Comics/9/Ek-Tha-Tiger-New |archive-date=12 November 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Games==\n* An android game base on the 2012 film has been released on the same year.<ref>http://gallery.mobile9.com/f/2821904/</ref><ref>http://phoneky.com/games/?id=j4j63435</ref>\n* Another game based on the 2012 film has been released on the same year, which is a Windows version game published by skf.<ref>http://www.hannygamez.net/2013/01/ek-tha-tiger-game.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2016894|Ek Tha Tiger}}\n* {{IMDb title|5956100|Tiger Zinda Hai}}\n* {{IMDb title|5956100|Tiger 3}}\n \n{{Tiger (franchise)}}\n\n[[Category:Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian film series]]\n[[Category:Spy film series]]\n[[Category:Films about the Research and Analysis Wing]]\n[[Category:Action film franchises]]\n[[Category:Thriller film series]]\n[[Category:Yash Raj Films]]\n", "name_user": "RYAZZ", "lab